    Purpose:  Provides BASIC programmers with an "event driven"
              windowing user interface toolbox.

    Features: LITE features mouse/software controlled overlapping
              "virtual" windows.  Virtual windows can be larger than
              the physical display.  Windows can be moved, hidden, re-
              sized, and scrolled under mouse or software control.
              The "window manager" uses "video recycling" (a technique
              of using excess video RAM scratch memory) to increase
              program speed and reduce memory requirements by up to
              24K.  Being "Event driven", once a display has been
              created, the whole thing can be managed with a single
              function call.  Setup user defined "hot keys" that
              bypass BASIC's clumsy internal events.  The "event
              manager" informs the user when a window was modified
              (moved, hidden, etc) or when a hot key or standard key
              was pressed.  ShareWare price is $25.00.

